 form was captured, rather than just stripping affixes. For 'የሚሽነሪ', the root 'ሚሽነሪ' was chosen as it is a direct loanword, and its function in the input context was adjectival. PROTOCOL 2 (THE JUDGE) and PROTOCOL 7 (THE FILTER) confirmed that all processed words and their roots were valid Amharic entries and met the minimum two-character length requirement. PROTOCOL 5 (THE TRANSLATOR) provided comprehensive English synonyms, and PROTOCOL 6 (THE GRAMMARIAN) assigned appropriate Parts of Speech, primarily 'Verb' for the relative clause forms and 'Conjunction' or 'Particle' for the split suffixes.","input_words":["የሚሸጠውና","የሚሸጡባቸውንም","የሚሸጥበትና","የሚሹኝም","የሚሻለውና","የሚሻላችሁን","የሚሻሩትንም","የሚሻተት","የሚሽቀነጠርበት","የሚሽነሪ","የሚሾፈረው","የሚሾፍሯት","የሚቀሉና","የሚቀላቀሉበትም","የሚቀላቀሉበትን","የሚቀላቀሉን","የሚቀላቀሏትን","የሚቀመት","የሚቀመጠዉ","የሚቀመጡትንና","የሚቀመጥባትን","የሚቀመጥባቸውና","የሚቀመጥብህም","የሚቀማጠሉት","የሚቀማጠልና","የሚቀምም","የሚቀሥፉ","የሚቀርብልዎ","የሚቀርጹልን","የሚቀሰቀሱት"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"}]